e people crying. <span class="_ _2"></span>They</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 y4b1 ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 ws86">told me that a child had died. <span class="_ _2"></span>The mother and f<span class="_ _6"></span>ather led me to the child<span class="_ _2"></span>,</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 y4b2 ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 ws2f">about four years old<span class="_ _2"></span>, w<span class="_ _3"></span>ho la<span class="_ _3"></span>y limp and cold on the bed. His mother said</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 y4b3 ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 wsae">that he had been sick for tw<span class="_ _3"></span>o da<span class="_ _2"></span>ys and had died some time later<span class="_ _3"></span>. I picked</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 y4b4 ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 wsa">up the child and hugged him to m<span class="_ _3"></span>y body<span class="_ _1f"></span>. I pray<span class="_ _3"></span>ed for God to help me, then</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 y4b5 ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 ws66">I read Psalm 46: “God is our refuge and strength, an ev<span class="_ _3"></span>er<span class="_ _3"></span>-present help in</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 y4b6 ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 wsfa">trouble. <span class="_ _2"></span>Therefore w<span class="_ _3"></span>e will not fear<span class="_ _2"></span>, though the ear<span class="_ _6"></span>th giv<span class="_ _3"></span>e wa<span class="_ _2"></span>y” </div><div class="t m0 x26 h42 yad8 ff21 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 ws0">(NIV).</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 yad9 ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 ws2">Then I knelt to pra<span class="_ _3"></span>y<span class="_ _1f"></span>. </div><div class="t m0 x4f h42 yada ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 wsd9">“God<span class="_ _2"></span>, I present m<span class="_ _3"></span>yself and this child to <span class="_ _1f"></span>Y<span class="_ _23"></span>ou. <span class="_ _1f"></span>Y<span class="_ _23"></span>ou can see his weeping</div><div class="t m0 xf h42 yadb ff22 fs6 fc4 sc0 ls1 ws155">family<span class="_ _1f"></span>. Come to us, Lord<span class="_ _2"></spa